  "text": "Previously studies showed DBC2 variations in expression is very frequent, while the gene mutation is rather infrequent [1, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , indicated that epigenetics events may play much more important role in loss of DBC2 expression. Recently, Shi and his colleagues analyzed promoter methylation and DBC2 gene expression in a bladder cancer research by MS-PCR and RT-PCR.",
